prompt:
Add a public function called ApplyComplex to Calculator.calr that uses a block lambda with multiple statements. The lambda should take an i32, check if it's positive, and return doubled value or 0.

Use this exact Calor block lambda syntax:
§F{f003:ApplyComplex:pub}
  §I{i32:x}
  §O{i32}
  §LAM{l001:n:i32}
    §IF{if001} (> n 0)
      §R (* n 2)
    §EL{if001}
      §R 0
    §/I{if001}
  §/LAM{l001}
  §R §C{l001}
    §A x
  §/C
§/F{f003}

The §LAM{id:param:type}...§/LAM{id} syntax creates a block lambda:
- id is the lambda identifier (used to call it)
- param is the parameter name
- type is the parameter type
- Can contain multiple statements
